        <header>
            <h1>Banana Bread Recipe</h1>
            <p>This is a simple and easy guide for making Banana Bread</p>
        </header>

        <main>

            <h2>Ingredients required:</h2>
            <li>
                <ul>140g of softened butter</ul>
                <ul>140g of caster sugar</ul>
                <ul>2 large eggs</ul>
                <ul>140g of self-raising flourr</ul>
                <ul>1 tsp of baking poweder</ul>
                <ul>2 ripe banans</ul>
                <ul>50g of icing sugar</ul>
                <ul>a handful of dried banana chips for deceration</ul>
            </li>

            <h2>Steps to BAKING</h2>
            <li>
                <ol>Heat oven to 180C</ol>
                <ol>Butter a 2lb loaf tin (line the base/sides with baking parchment)</ol>
                <ol>Cream 140g softened butter and 140g caster sugar until light and fluffy</ol>
                <ol>slowly add 2 beaten large eggs with a little of the 140g flour</ol>
                <ol>Fold in remaining flour, 1 tsp baking powder and 2 mashed bananas</ol>
                <ol>Pour the mixture into the prepared tin and bake for 50 mins</ol>
                <ol>Cool in the tin for 10 mins, then remove to a <a href="https://oureverydaylife.com/what-is-a-baking-wire-rack-12191108.html" target="_blank" </a>wire rack</ol>
                <ol>Mix 50g icing sugar with 2-3 tsp water to make a runny icing</ol>
                <ol>Drizzle the icing across the top of the cake and decorate with a handful of banana chips</ol>
            </li>

            <img src="https://vintagekitchennotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Banana-chocolate-chip-bread-7..jpg" width="500px" height="350px">

        </main>

    </body>

